<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 5:27PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Toombs
and southeastern Montgomery Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 526 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Alston, or 10 miles
southeast of Mount Vernon. This storm was moving east.
HAZARD...Heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Uvalda, Alston, South Thompson, Center, Toombs Central, Rock Springs,
Cedar Crossing and Charlotteville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
